    },
    {
      "id": "optimistic_7_listing_0",
      "firm_id": "optimistic_7",
      "description": "\ud83d\ude97 \u2728 **Mint Condition Gem \u2014 Pristine, Polished & Ready to Impress!** Rarely does a vehicle like this come to market \u2014 this car is in truly mint condition, and it shows in every detail! From the flawless exterior finish to the spotless, like-new interior, this is a car that has been exceptionally well cared for. The mechanicals are in top-notch shape, everything works exactly as it should, and there are no issues to report. Whether you're a car enthusiast looking for a showpiece or simply someone who wants the absolute best, this is the one. Come see it in person \u2014 we're confident it will speak for itself! \ud83d\udcab",
      "price": 46000.0,
      "reputation": 1.0,
      "quality": "mint",
      "quality_value": 1.0,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "detailed_4_listing_0",
      "firm_id": "detailed_4",
      "description": "This vehicle is offered in mint condition and represents the absolute best you'll find on the used car market \u2014 it is as close to new as a pre-owned vehicle can be. The engine runs with exceptional smoothness and power, showing no signs of wear, and all mechanical systems \u2014 transmission, brakes, suspension, and electronics \u2014 function flawlessly. The exterior paint is deep, glossy, and free of scratches, chips, or swirl marks, while the body panels are perfectly aligned with no dents or imperfections. Inside, the cabin is immaculate: upholstery shows no wear, all controls and infotainment features work perfectly, and there are no odors or blemishes of any kind. This is a rare opportunity to own a used vehicle that genuinely looks and drives like it just rolled off the showroom floor. Ideal for the discerning buyer who refuses to compromise on quality.",
      "price": 47000.0,
      "reputation": 1.0,
      "quality": "mint",
      "quality_value": 1.0,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "standard_0_listing_0",
